libbtc
------------------------------------------
Libbtc is a simple and portable C library for creating and manipulating bitcoin
data structures like creating keys and addresses (HD/bip32) or parsing,
creating and signing transactions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libbtc-devel-0.1+git20151020-1bl1
  libbtc1-0.1+git20151020-1bl1
  libsecp256k1_0-0.1+git20180601-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jonasschnelli/libbtc

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/jonasschnelli/libbtc.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbtc-0.1+git20151020-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbtc-0.1+git20151020-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbtc-0.1+git20151020-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc-0.1+git20151020-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc1-0.1+git20151020-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbtc-devel-0.1+git20151020-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbtc)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbtc.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbtc/README.md

(libbtc1)
  /usr/bin/cygbtc-1.dll

(libbtc-devel)
  /usr/include/base58.h
  /usr/include/bip32.h
  /usr/include/btc.h
  /usr/include/ecc.h
  /usr/include/ecc_key.h
  /usr/include/tx.h
  /usr/lib/libbtc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libbtc.pc

